The Kaduna State House of  Assembly Speaker, Hon. Yusuf Zailani, yesterday survived an impeachment plot but his deputy, Hon. Mukhtar Isa Hazo, was impeached following a vote of no confidence passed on him. Subsequently, a new deputy speaker, Hon. Isaac Auta Zankhai, from Kaura state constituency was elected and sworn in. The emergency plenary which was presided over by the clerk of the House Barrister Bello Zubair immediately swore in Hon. Zankhai amidst a rowdy session as a member tried to steal the maze. The new deputy speaker emerged shortly after 24 members of the Assembly passed a vote of no confidence on the former deputy speaker, Hon. Mukhtar Isa Hazo and impeached him. Meanwhile, shortly after the swearing in, member representing Makera Constituency, Hon. Liman Dahiru broke into the floor of the Assembly and seized the maze. However, before he could make his way out of the chamber, he was grabbed by the Sergeant at Arm, while other members quickly rushed in and retrieved the maze from him. The plenary thereafter ended in a rowdy session, while the aggrieved member, Dahiru Liman was dragged out of the chamber. Hon. Liman who had his dress torn, was later seen outside the Assembly chamber displaying anger over the impeachment of the former deputy speaker, Hon. Hazo.   